content.description: Start low on a decent edge at far right just above main horizontal crack. Move up using crimp slots to gain slopers in a cut out section of the rock. Use a small crimp and terrible, sloped sidepull on the right before a big move to the next edge. Use good holds, and make your way to top out.A detached block, down and right, that is an inch or so off the ground, is off for your feet.
content.location: Start is on the far right side of the face, on a decent edge just above the large horizontal crack#3 in beta photo

content.description: Start towards the center of wall on a fairly obvious, right-facing sidepull/undercling. Move up left to a sidepull crimp and then to a decent sloper. Bump your left hand out to a jug, and move up to an obvious crack with good holds. Reach right for a sharp crimp, and then make a throw for the third and final large horizontal crack. Finish with a decently committing topout that meets back up with Rosenberg.A detached block, down and right, that is an inch or so off the ground, is off for your feet.
content.location: Start left of Rosenberg on an obvious, large, sidepull/undercling feature.#1 in beta photo

content.description: Start matched on a tiny, horizontal crack above main crack system (just down and right of big sidepull feature). Move straight up through a missing chunk using small crimps staying right of Quagmire. Then use sharp, gaston crimp to move to the next horizontal crack. Continue up to top out.
content.location: Between Rosenberg and Quagmire, start on a thin, horizontal crack (you can get about a 1/3 pad crimp) just above the main horizontal crack and right/down of a sidepull.This is #2 in the beta photo.

content.description: Swamp Face East is a 17-20 foot wall to the right side of the main face. It is slightly less imposing wall than Swamp Face West but still has potentially daunting topouts. Despite its looks, with a few big horizontal crack features, there are some pretty challenging routes here. I am still in the process of cleaning the topout on the left side. More routes are to be added soon.
